"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Fix: Deferred condensation when live transcript is empty at commit time\n\n## Context\n\nCI run [22840528443](https://github.com/entireio/cli/actions/runs/22840528443) shows 42/43 cursor-cli E2E tests passing after our config isolation fix. The single failure is `TestMultiSessionSequential` â€” a **real-bug** in the CLI where condensation fails silently and is never retried.\n\n**Root cause:** When Cursor commits mid-turn, the post-commit hook tries to condense session data to `entire/checkpoints/v1`. For the second session, the live transcript file hasn't been flushed yet by Cursor, so `extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript` returns `\"live transcript is empty\"`. The checkpoint ID (`1f78a5eea34d`) was already written to the commit trailer by `prepare-commit-msg`, but:\n1. `condenseAndUpdateState` returns `false` â†’ `handler.condensed = false`\n2. Line 1017: `if handler.condensed && state.Phase.IsActive()` â†’ FALSE â†’ checkpoint ID NOT recorded in `TurnCheckpointIDs`\n3. At stop time, `finalizeAllTurnCheckpoints` finds `TurnCheckpointIDs` empty â†’ no-op\n4. Result: commit trailer points to nonexistent checkpoint metadata\n\n## Triage Classification\n\n| Test | Agent | Classification | Evidence |\n|------|-------|----------------|----------|\n| TestMultiSessionSequential | cursor-cli | **real-bug** | `entire.log` WARN: \"condensation failed: live transcript is empty\"; checkpoint `1f78a5eea34d` missing from `entire/checkpoints/v1` tree |\n\n## Fix: Record checkpoint IDs on attempt + deferred CondenseSession at stop time\n\n### File: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`\n\n#### Change 1: Add `condenseAttempted` flag to `postCommitActionHandler` (line 611)\n\nAdd a new field alongside `condensed`:\n```go\ntype postCommitActionHandler struct {\n    // ... existing fields ...\n    condensed          bool // true if condensation succeeded\n    condenseAttempted  bool // true if condensation was attempted (even if it failed)\n}\n```\n\n#### Change 2: Set `condenseAttempted` in handler methods (lines 650, 676)\n\nIn both `HandleCondense` and `HandleCondenseIfFilesTouched`, set `h.condenseAttempted = true` when `shouldCondense` is true (before calling `condenseAndUpdateState`):\n\n```go\nif shouldCondense {\n    h.condenseAttempted = true\n    h.condensed = h.s.condenseAndUpdateState(...)\n}\n```\n\n#### Change 3: Record checkpoint ID on attempt, not just success (line 1017)\n\nChange the guard from requiring success to requiring attempt:\n```go\n// Before:\nif handler.condensed && state.Phase.IsActive() {\n    state.TurnCheckpointIDs = append(...)\n}\n\n// After:\nif handler.condenseAttempted && state.Phase.IsActive() {\n    state.TurnCheckpointIDs = append(...)\n}\n```\n\nThis ensures the checkpoint ID is recorded even when condensation failed due to an empty transcript. The existing carry-forward logic (line 1027) still gates on `handler.condensed`, so carry-forward and shadow branch cleanup remain correct.\n\n#### Change 4: Handle `ErrCheckpointNotFound` in `finalizeAllTurnCheckpoints` (~line 2232)\n\nWhen `UpdateCommitted` returns `ErrCheckpointNotFound`, fall back to `CondenseSession`:\n\n```go\nupdateErr := store.UpdateCommitted(ctx, checkpoint.UpdateCommittedOptions{...})\nif updateErr != nil {\n    if errors.Is(updateErr, checkpoint.ErrCheckpointNotFound) {\n        // Checkpoint wasn't created at post-commit time (e.g., transcript was empty).\n        // Now that the full transcript is available, create it via CondenseSession.\n        _, condenseErr := s.CondenseSession(ctx, repo, cpID, state, nil)\n        if condenseErr != nil {\n            logging.Warn(logCtx, \"finalize: deferred condensation failed\", ...)\n            errCount++\n        } else {\n            logging.Info(logCtx, \"finalize: deferred checkpoint created\", ...)\n        }\n        continue\n    }\n    // Original error path for other failures\n    ...\n}\n```\n\n`CondenseSession` with `nil` committedFiles skips file filtering (line 158) and uses files from session data as-is â€” acceptable since files ARE agent-touched, just not filtered to a specific commit.\n\n### File: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/phase_postcommit_test.go`\n\nAdd unit tests:\n\n1. **`TestPostCommit_ActiveSession_RecordsTurnCheckpointIDs_OnCondensationFailure`** â€” ACTIVE session with empty transcript â†’ condensation fails â†’ verify `TurnCheckpointIDs` still contains the checkpoint ID\n2. **`TestFinalizeAllTurnCheckpoints_DeferredCondensation`** â€” `TurnCheckpointIDs` contains ID with no checkpoint on metadata branch + non-empty transcript on disk â†’ verify checkpoint created via `CondenseSession`\n3. **`TestFinalizeAllTurnCheckpoints_DeferredCondensation_TranscriptStillEmpty`** â€” Same setup but transcript still empty â†’ verify graceful failure (error logged, no panic)\n\n## Why This Is Safe\n\n- **No behavior change for working agents:** Claude Code, Gemini, etc. flush transcripts before committing. For them, `condenseAttempted = true` AND `condensed = true`, so `TurnCheckpointIDs` is recorded as before. `UpdateCommitted` succeeds at stop time â€” the `ErrCheckpointNotFound` fallback is never hit.\n- **Carry-forward unaffected:** The carry-forward logic (line 1027) still gates on `handler.condensed`, not `handler.condenseAttempted`. Shadow branch preservation (line 1072) also gates on `condensed`. Both remain correct.\n- **State remains consistent:** When condensation fails, `state.BaseCommit` stays at the old commit and the shadow branch is preserved â€” exactly what `CondenseSession` needs at stop time to find the shadow data.\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\nmise run fmt && mise run lint           # Static checks\nmise run test                           # Unit tests (includes new tests)\nmise run test:e2e:canary                # Canary (Vogon) â€” no API cost\nmise run test:e2e --agent cursor-cli    # Full cursor-cli suite â€” verify fix\n```\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before